 :cray: /kray/ n. 1. (properly, capitalized) One of the line of
supercomputers designed by Cray Research. 2. Any supercomputer at all. 3. The
{canonical} {number-crunching} machine. The term is actually the lowercased
last name of Seymour Cray, a noted computer architect and co-founder of the
company. Numerous vivid legends surround him, some true and some admittedly
invented by Cray Research brass to shape their corporate culture and image.